curam.util.client.model

Interface ComponentParameters

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    curam.util.client.model.internal.DefaultComponentParameters, FieldParameters

    public interface ComponentParameters
extends java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>
    A map for parameters to components that allows default values of parameters to be retrieved when no values were explicitly set. Not all parameters have a default value. The default values depend on the type of component and the specific parameter.

    • Method Detail

      • getWithDefault

        java.lang.String getWithDefault(java.lang.String name)

        Gets the value of the parameter, or its default value if the parameter is not defined. Not all parameters have default values, so null may be returned.

        The inherited get(String) method does not return the default value, so it is easy to determine if a value was set explicitly to the same value as the default value or if it was not set at all. This allows a renderer to impose different default values if necessary.

        Parameters:
        name - The name of the parameter.
        Returns:
        The value of the parameter, or its default value if the parameter is not defined.
